Gjallarhorn
===========

Gjallarhorn is a post-quantum fork of the Vuvuzela metadata-private messaging
system.

Upstream project
----------------

This codebase derives from:

  Vuvuzela
  https://github.com/vuvuzela/vuvuzela

Original authors:

  Copyright (c) 2015-2019 David Lazar
  with contributions from Jelle van den Hooff, Nickolai Zeldovich,
  and Matei Zaharia.

Upstream paper: David Lazar et al., "Vuvuzela: Scalable Private Messaging
Resistant to Traffic Analysis", SOSP 2015.
https://davidlazar.org/papers/vuvuzela.pdf

Fork
----

Gjallarhorn is maintained at https://github.com/oluies/gjallarhorn.
The fork was created to migrate the system to post-quantum cryptographic
primitives (hybrid X25519+ML-KEM-768 KEM, hybrid Ed25519+ML-DSA-65 signatures)
while preserving the original mixnet design, threat model, and license.

All files retained from the upstream project keep their original copyright
notices ("Copyright 2015 David Lazar. All rights reserved.") and license
headers. Modifications and new files carry their own copyright notices
alongside the upstream notice where appropriate.

